&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DIVISION OF WOMEN &amp; CHILDREN - THE JAMES COOK UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL &amp; FRIARAGE MATERNITY CENTRE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BAND 6 MIDWIFE (Various hours)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic and experienced midwives to join our midwifery team. South Tees Trust have a range of excellent development opportunities including Critical care team, public health team, NIPE, and future leadership opportunities Roles are available at James Cook and the Friarage Maternity Centre, working within our hospital, standalone birth centre, and community setting at both sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If working at The Friarage, you will be based primarily at Maternity Centre, Northallerton or at one of the Community Hubs, but may be required to work across site to meet service need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If based at James Cook, it will be a rotational post around all areas including the Friarage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;South Tees Hospitals Maternity Services is a progressive, innovative service that facilitates over 5000 deliveries per year on two sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are constantly striving to improve our services to women, babies and their families and the working environment for our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
